I'll wait for that, my Child.

260
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,367
Is that a promise?

261
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:46,967
Promise.

262
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:53,367
My child is very good.

263
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,600
Every time I design, Mother,

264
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:05,667
every time I have a fashion
show, you are my inspiration.

265
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,700
I want you to be proud of me.

266
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:15,233
I love you so much.

267
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:18,667
I miss you so much.

268
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:20,167
Hi, welcome to Celestial.

269
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:21,800
I'm Celeste.

270
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:23,200
Yes, I know you. I've watched

271
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:25,600
some of your fashion shows
online.

272
00:22:25,667 --> 00:22:27,667
Oh, thank you so much,
that's so sweet of you.

273
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:30,000
Is there anything
I can do for you?

274
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:33,100
Well, I still haven't gotten
my wedding gown yet.

275
00:22:33,167 --> 00:22:35,667
So, can I see some
of your designs?

276
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:38,600
Of course.
Let me get our designs.

277
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:40,733
Celeste, you have to see this.

278
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,167
The fashion reviews
just came out.

279
00:22:43,767 --> 00:22:44,367
Exciting.

280
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:48,433
- Major disaster
- Tale of a flop....

281
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:49,833
Spell ugly.

282
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,200
She's in love but her shows...

283
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:52,533
- are not.
- Not her best.

284
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,333
- Her designs
are way out of fashion.

285
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,867
- It's so out of fashion.

286
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,700
Celeste, I have to go.

287
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:06,800
Going too soon?

288
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:09,767
My mom just texted.

289
00:23:09,833 --> 00:23:11,867
She told me to check
on the House of Aurelia's.

290
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:15,133
Maybe I'll come back next time.

291
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,733
Well, have... have a good one.

292
00:23:44,133 --> 00:23:47,733
Dear, I really don't understand

293
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:50,233
why our clients are moving
to Aurelia.

294
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:53,367
The clients are traitors.

295
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:54,800
They have no loyalty.

296
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,700
Celeste, let them be.

297
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:58,367
We don't need them.

298
00:23:58,433 --> 00:23:59,633
Don't say that.

299
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:02,000
You know very well
that we need them.

300
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:03,933
You know that our bridal
collection

301
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,233
is Celestial's bread and butter.

302
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:09,200
Just like any fashion brand,
any fashion house,

303
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:10,467
that's where they make money.

304
00:24:10,533 --> 00:24:12,533
When the brides spend millions
and millions

305
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:14,267
to get their dream wedding.

306
00:24:15,633 --> 00:24:17,433
That's really where the fashion
industry makes money

307
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,567
and we're losing it.

308
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:21,067
I know Celeste.

309
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,267
I'm just easing your worries.

310
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:25,233
Okay, since you're lecturing me,

311
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:28,033
I'm sorry but I will
also lecture.

312
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:29,867
According to our business
projection,

313
00:24:29,967 --> 00:24:35,033
if we don't have 88 brides
to create their bridal gowns

314
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,933
for the second half
of this year,

315
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:41,467
we will lose 27% income
for this fiscal year.

316
00:24:41,533 --> 00:24:42,467
27%?

317
00:24:43,467 --> 00:24:44,133
That's big.

318
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:46,200
Oh my God.

319
00:24:47,667 --> 00:24:50,767
We need to find a way to make
our clients come back to us.

320
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:14,167
My God, Mother, the critics
of my fashion show came out.

321
00:25:14,233 --> 00:25:15,367
It pisses me off.

322
00:25:16,767 --> 00:25:18,200
I don't know.

323
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:19,867
They said a lot of things
about me

324
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,467
as if they bought my soul.

325
00:25:22,533 --> 00:25:24,500
They said I have no talent,
I have nothing.

326
00:25:24,567 --> 00:25:29,167
And one basher really said
something bad about me.

327
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:34,000
One account,
she's just one person.

328
00:25:34,067 --> 00:25:38,633
She made ten hashtags,
it pisses me off.

329
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:40,800
And the other one
who was not even invited,

330
00:25:40,867 --> 00:25:42,933
she's not even invited but she
said bad things about me.

331
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,767
How dare her.
She said I have no talent.

332
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:46,167
My talent is worthless.

333
00:25:46,233 --> 00:25:46,800
What is that?

334
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:51,567
It pisses me off.

335
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,333
It pisses me off.

336
00:26:02,567 --> 00:26:03,300
Sorry, Mother.

337
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:07,167
I want you to become proud of me
but...

338
00:26:10,567 --> 00:26:11,767
I wasn't able to do it.

339
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:44,433
Love, don't let those critics
get to you.

340
00:26:45,567 --> 00:26:47,500
Remember that doing your best
is more important

341
00:26:47,567 --> 00:26:48,367
than being the best.

342
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,233
Be gentle with yourself.

343
00:26:52,833 --> 00:26:54,633
Never forget for one moment

344
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:56,800
how truly amazing
and talented you are.

345
00:26:58,600 --> 00:26:59,167
Cheer up.

346
00:27:23,333 --> 00:27:24,433
Dad!

347
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,700
Tiffany, how was your vacation?

348
00:27:26,767 --> 00:27:28,200
I'm glad that you're back
from your ski trip

349
00:27:28,267 --> 00:27:29,200
with your cousins.

350
00:27:29,267 --> 00:27:30,900
It was fun, Dad.

351
00:27:30,967 --> 00:27:34,600
Thank you so much for asking
and I hope next time,

352
00:27:34,667 --> 00:27:37,000
you and mommy will be with us.

353
00:27:37,067 --> 00:27:38,167
If I have time, why not.

354
00:27:40,833 --> 00:27:41,600
Why don't you join us?

355
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,767
No, thanks, Dad.
We have our own reservation.

356
00:27:52,067 --> 00:27:53,667
Are you with someone?

357
00:27:53,733 --> 00:27:55,567
Yeah, my mom.

358
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,133
It's good to see you.

359
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,867
I was about to say
the same thing.

360
00:28:10,933 --> 00:28:13,033
This color looks so good on you.

361
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:14,400
You look great.

362
00:28:14,467 --> 00:28:16,867
I love it.

363
00:28:16,933 --> 00:28:17,333
Thank you.

364
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:22,633
Well, hello there.

365
00:28:22,733 --> 00:28:25,067
Well, Celeste, you look so pale.

366
00:28:25,133 --> 00:28:25,933
Are you sick?

367
00:28:27,367 --> 00:28:29,400
I'm perfectly fine.

368
00:28:29,467 --> 00:28:30,933
Are you sure?

369
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:34,800
Yeah, thank you
for your concern.

370
00:28:34,867 --> 00:28:36,667
Okay, if you say so.

371
00:28:36,733 --> 00:28:41,633
So, I've heard
that you are also invited

372
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:45,200
to my former sister-in-law's
grand birthday celebration.

373
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:48,667
I've talked to Vivian earlier.

374
00:28:48,733 --> 00:28:52,633
And she's so excited
to see you again.

375
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:57,600
Tiffany, you should have watched

376
00:28:57,667 --> 00:28:59,833
your Auntie Celeste's fashion
show.

377
00:28:59,900 --> 00:29:01,233
It was awesome.

378
00:29:01,300 --> 00:29:04,433
Oh, no thanks, Dad.

379
00:29:04,500 --> 00:29:07,733
I would rather watch
Mom's fashion events.

380
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:11,700
Anyway, mom is a better fashion
designer than your girlfriend.

381
00:29:11,767 --> 00:29:12,733
Tiffany!

382
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:13,233
What?

383
00:29:15,067 --> 00:29:16,500
I'm just telling the truth, Dad.

384
00:29:17,833 --> 00:29:20,967
Actually, I just read
the bad reviews

385
00:29:21,033 --> 00:29:23,067
about her latest designs.

386
00:29:23,133 --> 00:29:25,433
It was awful.

387
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:29,100
I mean, I know that you know it
already.

388
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,867
And yet you still support her?

389
00:29:33,267 --> 00:29:34,433
I don't want to sound rude

390
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:37,600
but I don't need to pretend,
Dad.

391
00:29:39,733 --> 00:29:40,633
I don't like her.

392
00:29:48,533 --> 00:29:49,567
I don't want to sound rude

393
00:29:49,633 --> 00:29:53,000
but I just don't need
to pretend.

394
00:29:54,533 --> 00:29:55,033
I don't like her.

395
00:29:57,333 --> 00:29:58,067
Reason?

396
00:29:59,533 --> 00:30:00,233
I just don't.

397
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:04,233
Mom, I lost my appetite.

398
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,500
Tiffany, you come back here

399
00:30:07,567 --> 00:30:08,800
and apologize
to your Auntie Celeste.

400
00:30:10,067 --> 00:30:10,300
No.

401
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:14,733
Enjoy your date.

402
00:30:19,633 --> 00:30:20,333
I'm so sorry about that.

403
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:22,700
It's fine.

404
00:30:57,033 --> 00:30:59,733
Celeste and I are secured
with our love for each other.

405
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:02,600
But we both know that it will
never be easy for Celeste

406
00:31:02,667 --> 00:31:03,733
to blend with the family.

407
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:06,000
You should separate from Tonito,
Celeste.

408
00:31:06,067 --> 00:31:09,300
Because even with your absolute
very best,

409
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:12,967
you will still never be good
enough for my brother.

410
00:31:14,033 --> 00:31:16,067
Mom, you still love my Dad?

411
00:31:16,133 --> 00:31:17,633
You will get hurt even more.

412
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:20,633
I will get hurt even more
if you will not do anything

413
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:22,567
for you and Dad
to get back together.

414
00:31:22,633 --> 00:31:23,800
Why did you call?

415
00:31:23,867 --> 00:31:25,967
They are on their way
to the provincial hospital.

416
00:31:26,033 --> 00:31:27,767
Father had a heart attack.

417
00:31:27,833 --> 00:31:28,533
Will you marry me?

418
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:35,367
You know I rarely ask anything
of you.

419
00:31:35,433 --> 00:31:36,867
Can you please go home?

420
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:40,700
It would be the best decision
you will make in your life.
